info.headline: Flood Advisory issued November 5 at 1:37AM PST until November 5 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Eureka CA
info.description:
* WHAT...Small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...A portion of northwest California, including the following county, southwestern Humboldt.
* WHEN...Until 700 AM PST.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Water over roadways.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 137 AM PST, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges indicated heavy rain. This will cause small stream flooding. Overflowing poor drainage areas will cause minor flooding in the advisory area. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 1.5 to 3 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Honeydew, Shelter Cove, Petrolia, Whitehorn, Ettersburg, Briceland and Capetown. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
